YELOW FEVER - BRAZIL (09)
*************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1] Fatal cases (Goias state, Federal District)
[2] Monkey deaths (Rondonia state)

******
[1] Fatal cases (Goias state, Federal District)
Date: 3 Feb 2008
Source: A Tarde Online [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.JW, edited]
<http://www.atarde.com.br/brasil/noticia.jsf?id=832920>


The Health Secretariat of Goias state confirmed on Friday [1 Feb
2008] one more death from yellow fever (YF), bringing the total for
2008 to 12 out of 17 confirmed cases in the state, with 2 more
under investigation and 12 suspect cases eliminated. The confirmation
was made by the Public Laboratory of the Federal District. The victim
was a man who worked in the fields and became ill in the rural zone
of the Planaltina de Goias, next to the Federal District. He was
unvaccinated, was hospitalized on 21 Jan 2008 and died on 29 Jan 2008.

Yesterday [2 Feb 2008], the Brazilian Ministry of Health confirmed
the death of a person who contracted YF in the Federal District, in
the suburbs of the capital, Brasilia. This is the 1st confirmed fatal
case in the Federal District.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <Promed-Port@promedmail.org>

******
[2] Monkey deaths (Rondonia state)
Date: 3 Feb 2008
Source: Rondonoticias [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.JW, edited]
<http://www.rondonoticias.com.br/showNew.jsp?CdMateria=70664&CdTpMateria=7>


The National Health Foundation (Funasa) is investigating monkey
deaths suspected to be from YF in the rural zone of Jaru
municipality, Rondonia state, where 6 monkeys have been found dead,
and more have been reported by residents in other parts of the
municipality.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <Promed-Port@promedmail.org>

[Map of areas with epizootic monkey deaths:
<http://portal.saude.gov.br/portal/arquivos/pdf/nota_tecnica_epizootias_macacos_jan_2008_v2.pdf>

